{"ts": "2026-06-09T22:55:57.738693+00:00", "update": {"model": {"messages": [{"type": "ai", "data": {"content": "Unfortunately, the repository's personal access token doesn't have write permissions, so I cannot push changes directly. However, here's a summary of everything I've prepared and the exact changes needed:\n\n---\n\n## Summary of Issue #1 — \"Add authentication API docs\"\n\n### Acceptance Criteria\n- ✅ `docs/api/authentication.md` — flesh out the stub\n- ✅ `mkdocs.yml` — add `Authentication` to the API nav\n- ✅ Existing validation (`make validate`) will still pass (it checks for `site_name` and `nav` keys, which remain present)\n\n### Change 1: `docs/api/authentication.md` (replace stub)\n\n```markdown\n# Authentication\n\nAll API requests require authentication via a Bearer token in the `Authorization` header.\n\n```\nAuthorization: Bearer <your-api-token>\n```\n\n## Obtaining a token\n\nTokens are issued through the `/auth/token` endpoint. Provide your client credentials to receive a short-lived access token.\n\n## Token lifetime\n\nTokens expire after **3600 seconds** (one hour). Once expired, request a new token using the same endpoint.\n\n## Error responses\n\nAuthentication failures return a `401` status code. See [Errors](errors.md) for the response format.\n```\n\n### Change 2: `mkdocs.yml` (add authentication link under API nav)\n\nThe `nav` section's `API` sub-items should become:\n\n```yaml\n  - API:\n      - Overview: api/overview.md\n      - Authentication: api/authentication.md   # <-- new line\n      - Errors: api/errors.md\n```\n\n### Limitation\n\nAll three write attempts (`create_or_update_file` × 2 and `push_files`) returned **403 — Resource not accessible by personal access token**. The repository token does not have push/write access. To complete this issue, someone with write access would need to apply the two changes above manually, or the token's permissions would need to be escalated.", "additional_kwargs": {"refusal": null}, "res